comment_data.body: Have you contacted Jetbrains about this? Without better repro info there's not much we can do.

No, I didn't. I suspect it's some interaction between IntelliJ and the Dart server.

Every time I saved my file IntelliJ would crash, so I closed IntelliJ and the dart.exe process, opened my file on a text editor, edited it, saved it, restarted my PC (as a precaution) and so far the problem hasn't surfaced again. 

For the way IntelliJ was behaving I imagine maybe the file was in a bad state, something conflicting in IntelliJ cache maybe and the dart analysis server was deadlocking it in some way when it tried to analyze the files new content.
It just happened again. Since I think this is dart related, could you please include here someone at IntelliJ that deals with the dart plugin?
Wow, sorry about that. Let's bring @devoncarew and @jwren in for some brainstorming. Also @alexander-doroshko might have some insight.
Please, because I am losing a ton of work with the failure, basically everything I typed since my last save point.

FYI this is my monitor right now (its supposed to be an IntelliJ Window):

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8120472/62554944-71eca100-b848-11e9-8bd1-f0c819f31702.png)
You might want to go back to 2019.1 to keep from losing work.

Go grab and attach relevant logs, they can be found at `Help` > `Show Log in <OS Finder equivalent>`

I'm guessing the IntelliJ from your log that is causing concern is this one, `IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate Edition (version 2019.2)`, it looks like the settings & preference directory that is being used is from 2019.1-  just something to rectify to rule it out.
Right, logs and auto-saved thread dumps should help. Use Help -> Compress Logs... and attach the resulting zip here.

@feinstein Thank you for the logs! It looks like there's a problem with the Dart Structure View. An infinite loop may happen. I'll fix this ASAP and publish the updated Dart plugin. As a workaround, you may keep the Structure tool window closed.
ohh thanks for the quick fix!
Filed an issue here: https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/WEB-40544 and fixed. Dart plugin build is in progress.

Thank you @alexander-doroshko.

After the dart plugin is pushed, record the version here so we can close this issue.

@alexander-doroshko while you are at it, could you take a look at dart tests?

IIRC when I opened a test file, IntelliJ would give me test shortcuts (Run/Debug Arrows) right next to the `test` and `group` blocks, but they are all gone now. Maybe this was never added and I am just getting confused with Java?

(Do you prefer that I open this at youtrack? I just thought here the triage will be quicker).

___________________________________

EDIT: Never mind, I found it already opened at #3398.
Dart plugin updates with the fix are available: version 191.8369 and 192.6262.13.
